{"key":"processedPost-11060725","value":{"id":11060725,"first":11058024,"last":11060823,"when":1252985330,"utime":"09/15/09 06:28 AM","cleanedPost":"Cracker dry, then seal in vacuum bags.&nbsp; I have some that have been sealed for nearly ten years now.&nbsp; Every year we break out a bag and sample the contents.&nbsp; They're still just as good as the day we bagged them.&nbsp; Each bag gets a food-grade silica gel packet and a food-grade oxygen absorber packet.&nbsp; That's the key to indefinite storage.&nbsp; Ziplock bags are gas permeable so eventually the desiccant will saturate with moisture and the mushrooms will be ruined.&nbsp; Vacuum bags are a total seal, as are mason jars, which also work if you'll pull a vacuum in them.<br />RR"}}